.TH "nd_uuid_store" 9 "nd_uuid_store" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nd_uuid_store \- common implementation for writing 'uuid' sysfs attributes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nd_uuid_store
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "u8 **uuid_out "  ","
.BI "const char *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
container device for the uuid property
.IP "uuid_out" 12
uuid buffer to replace
.IP "buf" 12
raw sysfs buffer to parse
.IP "len" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Enforce that uuids can only be changed while the device is disabled
(driver detached)
LOCKING: expects \fBnd_device_lock\fP is held on entry
